latestIgtvVideos.title: GRWM for the beach 🏖
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This video is to give you an idea of how I got ready for the beach on my last vacation.
Firstly, I have an acne sticker on my face. I never try to shoot using filters because let’s face it filters are fun but not real. I want you to see my real skin with the makeup. 
Some tips for a beach makeup:
- try using cream products as much as you can because you will tend to sweat a lot and creams wear-off naturally.
- the only reason I used powder all over my face was to prevent it from fading fast due to face mask.
- try carrying multi-purpose products. Saves you time and face.
- Opt for more peachy/orangy tones. Looks ready good with a tan.
- Keep your base as much light as possible. Do not layer a lot.

Products used:
Primer: @tartecosmetics Sea Quench hydrating Primer

latestIgtvVideos.title: NIGHTTIME SKINCARE ROUTINE - UPDATED
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
.
Tadaaaa, finally a new IGTV after ages since I have all the time now to create and you have all the time to watch😬😬 .
.
.
Products used:
Face wash: @cerave hydrating face cleanser
Pro tip: massage your face for atleast 60 secs with any cleanser for it to be effective.
Clay mask: @aztec.clay 
Pro tip: use it once or max twice a week and don’t leave for more than 5-7 mins. It causes redness but will settle in a bit.
@facehalo : to wipe off mask
Serum: @deciem Ordinary Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1%
Pro Tip: niacinamide is a water-soluble vitamin that works with the natural substances in your skin to help visibly minimize enlarged pores, tighten lax pores, improve uneven skin tone, soften fine lines and wrinkles, diminish dullness, and strengthen a weakened surface.
Night cream: @freshbeauty lotus youth preserve night cream
Pro tip: wait for min 10 secs between all product applications for them to sink into your skin.
Occasional cream: @weleda skin food Ultra-rich cream.
Eye cream: @olehenriksen banana bright eye cream
Pro tip: massage gently with your ring finger.
Topical medication: tretinoin cream 0.05%
Pro tip: decrease the number and severity of acne pimples and promote quick healing of pimples that do develop.
Lip balm: @freshbeauty hydrating lip balm.
.
Song: @billieeilish .
